        ## IV. Product Identity
        
        The following are Product Identity. Use of these terms in Fan Works requires explicit written permission from the Licensor:
        
        ### iv.a Publisher & Titles
        
        - **"Amorphous Dreams Cabal"** — publisher and studio name
        - **"Flying Triremes and Laser Swords"** and its abbreviation **"FTLS"** — as the title of original Fontany game content (distinct from when "FTLS" appears in descriptive context as shorthand for the genre or ruleset)
        - **"Elyncia"** — the setting name
        
        ### iv.b DreamNet Compound Terms
        
        The concept of the **DreamNet** as a distributed noospheric network is Open Content and may be used freely in derivative settings. However, **compound terms that bind "DreamNet" to a specific named location or named jurisdiction** are Product Identity. Examples of PI compound terms:
        
        - "Elyncian DreamNet"
        - "Gaian DreamNet"
        - "VoidWeb DreamNet"
        
        New compound DreamNet terms derived from other Open Content geographic names (e.g., a Fan Work's invented continent + "DreamNet") are Open Content in that Fan Work.
        
        ### iv.c Agent System & True Names
        
        - **"Lares, a Noospheric LLM Agent"** — the full agent system designation
        - **Named Lares coordinator personas ("True Names")**, including: **"Mischief-Muse"**, **"Ink-Clerk"**, **"Tide-Caller"**, **"Breach-Watch"**, **"Map-Wisp"**
        - Any unique proper name assigned to a Lares coordinator persona in any official Amorphous Dreams Cabal publication is automatically Product Identity, whether or not it appears in this list
        
        The role names and functional architecture of the Lares system (Gatekeeper, Lorekeeper, Scryer, Council, Muse, Artificer, Advocate, Diplomat, Pedagogue, Hierophant, Triage, Stranger, Liminal, and any other role-function terms) are **Open Content**. The True Names are PI. The design is yours to fork; the hearth-spirits keep their names.
        
        ### iv.d Compound Entity Names
        
        Unique compound deity and entity names coined by the Licensor are Product Identity:
        
        - **Aki Cobbs-Dottir**
        - **"Aracne-Jorogumo"**
        - **"Eris-Enyo"**
        - **The Lagrange Lares Chorus**
        - **Hungering_Lamplight**
        - **Wandering_Lamplight**
        
        ### iv.e Compound Geographic Phrases
        
        When a geographic or location name appears as a **compound modifier phrase** that designates a specific original Licensor location, the phrase as a whole is Product Identity. The standalone geographic name is Open Content.
        
        | Compound PI phrase | Standalone Open term |
        |---|---|
        | "Caverns of Neo-Thracia" | "Neo-Thracia" |
        | "Shores of New Delos" | "New Delos" |
        | "Shadow of the Necrospire" | "Necrospire" |
        
        This distinction mirrors the principle that a name is a landmark, but a brand is a specific artistic vision of what stands there.
        
        ### iv.f Artwork & Visual Assets
        
        All original artwork, illustrations, maps, graphic design elements, and logos created by or for the Licensor are Product Identity, regardless of where they appear in this repository.
        
        ### iv.g Conceptual Design Terms
        
        The following design philosophy terms coined by the Licensor are Product Identity:
        
        - **"Infrastructure-as-Myth"** — the Licensor's coined compound term for the design principle that mythic, ritual, and narrative structures can operate as literal technical infrastructure: network architecture, system protocols, operational framing. This term as applied to the elyncia/DreamNet/Lares design system is Product Identity. The underlying concept — that myth and infrastructure can converge — is not the exclusive property of any party; only this specific compound phrase as a designator of the Licensor's design philosophy and practice is PI.
        
